  <summary date="2009-01-31T14:47:59Z" status="Introduced in House">Recognizes the threat that the spread of radical Islamist terrorism and Iranian adventurism in Africa poses to the United States, our allies, and interests.

Acknowledges the commitment and cooperation of some African governments and regional organizations to deny the use of their territory to radical Islamist terrorist organizations.

Calls on the U.S. government to work with governments in Africa to pursue an antiterrorism campaign.</summary>
